article.headline: Loyola Chi 89, Northern Illinois 86
article.story: BALTIMORE (AP) -- Navy's Corey Johnson scored a team-high 21 points and sparked a late run that helped the Midshipmen rally for an 89-86 victory over Loyola on Sunday night. The win gave new Navy coach Billy Lange his first victory at the school. Loyola coach Jimmy Patsos also is in his first year, but his Greyhounds now are 0-2 and have lost 11 straight going back to last season. Johnson scored nine of Navy's points during a game-closing 19-9 run. The Midshipmen trailed for much of the second half, but Johnson's basket with 1:17 left gave Navy the lead for good at 83-82. David Hooper (18 points) and Matt Fannin (14 points) also helped a Navy team that struggled offensively for much of last season. Charlie Bell led Loyola with a game-high 26 points. Bell scored 20 in a frantic first half that saw Loyola take a 52-49 lead at the break. Freddie Stanback (19 points) and Brad Farrell (13 points) also helped, but the Greyhounds faded in the final minutes.
